From 4d6d71dcdd29704679e9f3240ac1263729b5b1a3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 11:11:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix(chat): prevent duplicate TTS and show voice loading
 indicator

- speakLuna now uses AbortController: each new TTS call cancels any
  in-flight request from the previous call, so duplicate greetings
  (null-child vs loaded-child) never result in two voices playing
- Greeting useEffect returns a cleanup that aborts the chat fetch,
  preventing a stale greeting from completing after the child loads
- ttsLoading state drives a small bar-chart animation in the Luna
  status strip so the 4-5s TTS latency feels intentional, not broken
- Mute button also aborts the in-flight TTS fetch immediately

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_015q4ocvtUkmcgg6tzScAi1d
